The paper proposes a method for fingerprint spoof detection using deep learning techniques and evaluates it on publicly available datasets. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-categories. The use of DenseNet and patch attention networks also suggests that the paper may be relevant to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Additionally, the evaluation of cross-sensor, cross-material and cross-dataset performance suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
